[thinking] 
[thinking] **Analyzing native build execution**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether native analysis can look at both actual execution and static analysis. It seems that nativeTestCompile focuses on dynamic access output without actually running tests. I’m wondering if tests happen during image build. If the dynamic report includes call sites from the build time, it doesn’t execute test code. “Covered” might mean that a call site is reachable and has the necessary metadata. To ensure everything's covered during the build, maybe I need to rethink how to handle branches.
