[thinking] I'm thinking about whether we can use class initialization at runtime. If MemoryUnmapper is initialized during the native image process, it’s possible that the analysis won’t recognize INVOKE_CLEANER, making both branches reachable. With the build argument `--initialize-at-run-time=org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper`, static finals might not be folded, meaning that both branches in the unmap function could be reachable. But I wonder if line 36 might not be covered in the native compile, which could lead to some information being lost.
