r3hKuGf5ICRvLyHVQlynHBTwLleI17Bk-AkA9dcvFB__1dA4OHtWMIxVpJl5AGQ4J4-Ajc08iMDGnopPczNK3DTUYcQZ9Ov7rTdsR7VIjusd2cT4uM0nJKDP6SmyNBigpWv2DtJTk4C86BgRd5WRnBTrit75JesNEPKyYjW6QygWY2ZW7aZVoEiebA5y32cBa_HY2NwezxcXrSQOTdaGhAU_l8kUPMVri8oKK-tOfXVmVO4gviDa2nlcOhUpe634TWEbRtuP01EAll7ZuJh4CaHrecvmPmoWvPbsprErAXtt4P_-Hux1dYQGH0lhkazgOgGZjuNKLP5IDP60mPbz5oGwATgJvsKnCI4eSvyP5ClxBvaH4Zb2oGrkRWhVpO59UdlSfeWuVceKSfEfmM7GdMfnOxZMhuOhuQ0xMtLipB5gXnUeg11YoB9yjYcVqQyLdpJ1Ow3jUGK9j03CPKKLv7235XWU4bqPKFP6k0_W40RKJ7UsX7YYXad2\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native image build details**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the dynamics of nativeTestCompile and its focus on builds rather than executions. The native image build seems to analyze during the build process instead of actual tests. I’m pondering whether the dynamic accesses are marked as reachable and the implications of build arguments like TrackDynamicAccess. I notice that class initialization can happen at build time, particularly for classes referenced in tests. This is quite a complex setup to navigate!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing native build execution**\\n\\nI'm considering whether native analysis can look at both actual execution and static analysis. It seems that nativeTestCompile focuses on dynamic access output without actually running tests. I’m wondering if tests happen during image build. If the dynamic report includes call sites from the build time, it doesn’t execute test code. “Covered” might mean that a call site is reachable and has the necessary metadata. To ensure everything's covered during the build, maybe I need to rethink how to handle branches.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class initialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether we can use class initialization at runtime. If MemoryUnmapper is initialized during the native image process, it’s possible that the analysis won’t recognize INVOKE_CLEANER, making both branches reachable. With the build argument `--initialize-at-run-time=org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper`, static finals might not be folded, meaning that both branches in the unmap function could be reachable. But I wonder if line 36 might not be covered in the native compile, which could lead to some information being lost.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Improving build.gradle**\\n\\nI'm looking at the current build.gradle and confirming that the test is already included in the previous commit. I see that there's an unstaged index, which means I can edit build.gradle. Now, I want to enhance it further by possibly adding the build argument `--initialize-at-run-time=org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper`. I'm wondering if that’s broad enough or if I need to be more focused in my approach. Let's figure out the best way to improve this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_djt305Qa5zQlL0NzQfgzbwH5|fc_093e922d7e18f3ef0169f108bbc7cc8192b9159e886201de10", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class DynamicAccessUtils|TrackDynamicAccess|Preserve\" tests/tck-build-logic/src/main -g '*.java' -g '*.groovy'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1107, "output": 1326, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40321, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777404071556, "responseId": "resp_093e922d7e18f3ef0169f108a838f88192b50d5b44d69e6116"}}
