uild argument `--initialize-at-run-time=org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper`, static finals might not be folded, meaning that both branches in the unmap function could be reachable. But I wonder if line 36 might not be covered in the native compile, which could lead to some information being lost.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Improving build.gradle**\\n\\nI'm looking at the current build.gradle and confirming that the test is already included in the previous commit. I see that there's an unstaged index, which means I can edit build.gradle. Now, I want to enhance it further by possibly adding the build argument `--initialize-at-run-time=org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper`. I'm wondering if that’s broad enough or if I need to be more focused in my approach. Let's figure out the best way to improve this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_djt305Qa5zQlL0NzQfgzbwH5|fc_093e922d7e18f3ef0169f108bbc7cc8192b9159e886201de10", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class DynamicAccessUtils|TrackDynamicAccess|Preserve\" tests/tck-build-logic/src/main -g '*.java' -g '*.groovy'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1107, "output": 1326, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40321, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777404071556, "responseId": "resp_093e922d7e18f3ef0169f108a838f88192b50d5b44d69e6116"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_djt305Qa5zQlL0NzQfgzbwH5|fc_093e922d7e18f3ef0169f108bbc7cc8192b9159e886201de10", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtils.java:18:public abstract class DynamicAccessUtils {\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtils.java:20:    private static final String TRACK_DYNAMIC_ACCESS_PREFIX = \"-H:TrackDynamicAccess=path=\";\nt